Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [telegram] <PTYX11> Jumblr works yes

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [telegram] <fellowsheep> Thanks (re @PTYX11: Jumblr works yes)

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [telegram] <PTYX11> Jumblr makes coins fungible

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [telegram] <PTYX11> It does it by making a series of transactions that create a "Blackbox" where you cant decipher what is being mixed. You can only see what goes in and comes out. However, what comes out is all denominated in the same amounts and in timeframes that can be delayed. So it's difficult to trace once KMD is Jumblrd.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [telegram] <PTYX11> The sequence is transparent - > private then private - > private and finally a private - > to public
